<br>
&quot;Clerics can out damage/nuke/heal paladins&quot;<br>
<br>
About half true, half false. Of course clerics can outheal paladins (in situations where complete heal of one person is the goal, but not in the situation where group healing is the goal.)<br>
<br>
Out nuke? Hmmm, I'm not sure ... my best nuke (at 52 mind you) is for 542, unless I'm going against undead when I have a 758. If that's outdamaging paladins on nukes, so be it -- it's at the low end of the DD scale among casters.<br>
<br>
Out melee? This is where the people are spinning out of control comparing bad data. I've seen parses where a cleric (through all damage sources) is generating 45dps -- in a group where they are not main tanking, where the mob has been slowed, where the cleric has been hasted and buffed, and where the mob is low blue. The parses that I've seen of clerics really operating solo in abilities are showing something more like 23 dps, in great part because neither the cleric or their pet can actually take a licking because of lack of any real damage mitigation skills. So those cases where I've seen paladins complain that clerics are out-damaging, they are almost always comparing their solo damage to one of the &quot;highest dps situations&quot; for the cleric, which is no more of a fair comparison of DPS than saying that druids can get 135dps with one spell (which they can, mind you, just only for a couple of minutes before they are OOM.)<br>
<br>
The hammer owns, if it was in the hands of someone with a decent to-hit table. The parses that I'm seeing of clerics using these new toys shows melee damage at about 15% of the total output, or about half of what the pet is doing. What saves the clerics is that they can proc on a miss, so it's really just a form of a DD. Clerics soloing undead are finding it is still more mana efficient to root/nuke than to melee with this puppy.<br>
<br>
And, all of this stuff isn't available to a cleric until 56. Notin' for dis dorf mind you. Not that most of us as clerics ever expected or wanted or asked for this kind of upgrade.<br>
<br>
Yenadil wrote: &quot;In excess of 100dps in some cases.&quot;<br>
<br>
No, that's not true, Yenadil. Go to the cleric boards, look at the log parses that people are posting. The only time I've ever seen &quot;in excess of 100dps&quot; mentioned is in contexts like this -- reported as rumor without a log parse to point to.<br>
<br>
Yenadil also wrote:<br>
<br>
&quot;With self buffs only, at lvl 56 a cleric using the new hammer against undead can manage a low 40's DPs.&quot;<br>
<br>
I hate to tell you this, but as a level 52 cleric without the hammer and fighting undead I can manage the low 40s of DPS -- but it is done through root/nuke/dot/fear tactics to avoid having to complete heal/divine aura/run like hell. Only really works against undead, I can take low blues. 40 dps in a situational basis is hardly unbalancing (see above figures for druids for example) or new against undead solo.<br>
<br>
Yenadil wrote: &quot;In comparison, a lvl 56 paladin with epic and SCHW averages about a 38 dps&quot;<br>
<br>
Yenadil, you're doing the same thing again ... you're quoting a paladin solo versus a situation cleric in a group. Heh heh ... so funny to watch people bend statistics.<br>
<br>
Ssyrax: &quot;Clerics have become so unbalanced its not even funny. Reports on the monkly boards of them doing lvl 60 rogue damage?&quot;<br>
<br>
Lies, damned lies and statistics! Show me a log parse of that. Not a message saying &quot;dude, I heard that&quot; but someone parsing damage tables. Most of the cleric community considers that statement a myth -- no one in cleric boards can reproduce that, nor can they reproduce the &quot;outdamaging a level 60 monk with epic fists&quot; story either. I have seen a few logs where clerics are outdamaging beastlords *giggle*<br>
<br>
Too much ranting for me, I'm just sick of hearing people say how uber this thing is that I didn't get when I know that what they are saying doesn't match up with the reams of data coming in (that I'm looking at hoping to figure out whether to scream how stupid this &quot;new vision&quot; of clerics is.)<br>
<br>
